      <h2>8. Using AI Effectively</h2>

      <p>I use AI (Claude, Cursor, GitHub Copilot) for ~80% of my coding. Here's how to make it work for you:</p>

      <h3>Before You Start Coding</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Give context:</strong> "I'm contributing to a data science portfolio site built with Astro. Here's the project structure: [paste tree output]"</li>
        <li><strong>Share examples:</strong> "Here's an existing component that does something similar: [paste code]"</li>
        <li><strong>State your goal:</strong> "I want to create X that does Y"</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>While Coding</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Explain errors:</strong> Paste the full error message and the relevant code</li>
        <li><strong>Ask for explanations:</strong> "Why does this code do X? I expected Y"</li>
        <li><strong>Request alternatives:</strong> "This works but feels clunky. Is there a cleaner way?"</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Prompts That Work Well</h3>
      
      <div class="not-prose my-4 border border-border p-4 bg-muted/30">
        <p class="text-sm font-mono">"I'm looking at [file]. Explain what it does and how it connects to the rest of the app."</p>
